      <section anchor="tnumber">
        <name>TNumber</name>
        <t>
          This is the abstract class with static factory methods named 
          <em><strong>from* (pronounced 'from star')</strong></em>. The 
          <em><strong>from*</strong></em> methods MAY be overloaded or MAY have 
          extension methods depending on if your language allows method overloading.
        </t>
        <t>
          i.e. <xref target="java-language-specification" format="none" sectionFormat="bare">Java</xref> 
          Psudocode
        </t>
        <sourcecode type="java">
  String s = TNumber.from((float) 10.19).toString();
  TNumber t = TNumber.from("10.19");
  println(t.getType()); // Prints TDecimal
  float f = ((TDecimal) t).toFloat();
  BigDecimal b = ((TDecimal) t).toBigDecimal();
        </sourcecode>
        <t>
          i.e. <xref target="typescript" format="none" sectionFormat="bare">Typescript 
          / ECMA Script</xref> Psudocode
        </t>
        <sourcecode type="typescript">
  let s : string = TNumber.fromNumber(10.19).toString();
  let t : TDecimal = TNumber.fromBigDecimal(new BigDecimal("10.19"));
  number n = t.toNumber(); // IEEE 754 per the ECMA Script standard
        </sourcecode>
      </section>
  
      <section anchor="tint">
        <name>TInt</name>
        <t>
          This is the representation of <xref target="integers" format="none" 
          sectionFormat="bare">Ten10b Integers</xref>. It SHOULD extend T number, 
          when extension is available. It SHOULD provide various methods 
          <em><strong>to* (pronounced 'to star')</strong></em> which convert the 
          TInt into the local language's class or type system.
        </t>
        <t>
          It MUST return false from the <em><strong>isDecimalOrFraction</strong></em> 
          method. It MUST return false to the <em><strong>isDecimal</strong></em> 
          method. It MUST return false from the <em><strong>isFraction</strong></em> 
          method.
        </t>
        <t>
          It MUST return false from the <em><strong>isLoop</strong></em> method. 
          It MAY provide a true or false answer to the <em><strong>isBig</strong></em> 
          method. When the <em><strong>isBig</strong></em> method returns false, it 
          MUST throw an exception or error when the <em><strong>toBigInt</strong></em> 
          is called.
        </t>
      </section>
  
      <section anchor="tfraction">
        <name>TFraction</name>
        <t>
          TFraction is the representation of a <xref target="integer-fractions" 
          format="none" sectionFormat="bare">Ten10b Integer Fraction</xref>. It 
          MUST return a TInt result from the <em><strong>getNumerator</strong></em> 
          and <em><strong>getDenominator</strong></em> methods. It MUST return true 
          if either the numerator or denominator returns true for the 
          <em><strong>isBig</strong></em> method.
        </t>
        <t>
          It MUST return true from the isDecimalOrFraction method. It MUST return 
          false from the <em><strong>isDecimal</strong></em> method. It MUST return 
          true from the <em><strong>isFraction</strong></em> method. It MUST return 
          false from the <em><strong>isLoop</strong></em> method.
        </t>
      </section>
  
      <section anchor="tintloop">
        <name>TIntLoop</name>
        <t>
          TFraction is the representation of a <xref target="integer-fractions" 
          format="none" sectionFormat="bare">Ten10b Integer Loop</xref>.
          It MUST return the next digit when the <em><strong>next</strong></em> 
          method is called.
        </t>
        <t>
          It MUST return false from the isDecimalOrFraction method. It MUST return 
          false from the <em><strong>isDecimal</strong></em> method. It MUST return 
          true from the <em><strong>isFraction</strong></em> method. It MUST return 
          true from the <em><strong>isLoop</strong></em> method.
        </t>
      </section>
  
      <section anchor="tdecimal">
        <name>TDecimal</name>
        <t>
          TFraction is the representation of a <xref target="decimals" format="none" 
          sectionFormat="bare">Ten10b Decimal</xref>. It MAY return either true or 
          false from the <em><strong>isBig</strong></em> method, and SHOULD base 
          this decision around the semantics of the libraries in the language it 
          is implemented in.
        </t>
        <t>
          TDecimals MUST be implemented using a BigInteger type (i.e. 
          <xref target="ecma-script" format="none" sectionFormat="bare">BigInt</xref>, 
          <xref target="java-language-specification" format="none" sectionFormat="bare"
          >BigInteger</xref>) for the numeric part (integer and decimal parts), 
          which conforms to <xref target="math-international-standard" format="none" 
          sectionFormat="bare">ISO/IEC 10967 integer datatype section 5.1 / 
          International Math Standard.</xref> TDecimals MUST also be implemented 
          using a 2nd BigInteger type (i.e. <xref target="ecma-script" format="none" 
          sectionFormat="bare">BigInt</xref>, <xref target="java-language-specification" 
          format="none" sectionFormat="bare">BigInteger</xref>) to track the 
          number of <xref target="base-10" format="none" sectionFormat="bare"
          >(base/radix 10) decimal places</xref>, which conforms to 
          <xref target="math-international-standard" format="none" sectionFormat="bare"
          >ISO/IEC 10967 integer datatype section 5.1 / International Math 
          Standard.</xref>
        </t>
        <t>
          It MUST return true from the <em><strong>isDecimalOrFraction</strong></em> 
          method. It MUST return true from the <em><strong>isDecimal</strong></em> 
          method. It MUST return false from the <em><strong>isFraction</strong></em> 
          method. It MUST return false from the <em><strong>isLoop</strong></em> 
          method.
        </t>
      </section>
  
      <section anchor="tdecimalloop">
        <name>TDecimalLoop</name>
        <t>
          TFraction is the representation of a <xref target="decimal-loops" 
          format="none" sectionFormat="bare">Ten10b Decimal Loops</xref>.
          The <em><strong>to* (pronounced to star)</strong></em> methods will have 
          implementation algorithms based on the language implementation details.
        </t>
        <t>
          It MUST return true from the <em><strong>isDecimalOrFraction</strong></em> 
          method. It MUST return true from the <em><strong>isDecimal</strong></em> 
          method. It MUST return false from the <em><strong>isFraction</strong></em> 
          method. It MUST return true from the <em><strong>isLoop</strong></em> 
          method.
        </t>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section anchor="commentary">
      <name>Commentary</name>
      <t>
        The motivation for this internet draft is largely a vague gap that 
        exists between the <xref target="json-rfc-8259" format="none" 
        sectionFormat="bare">JSON RFC 8259</xref> and the <xref target="ecmascript-2025" 
        format="none" sectionFormat="bare">ECMAScript specification</xref>. 
        Instead of providing clarity (which is the purpose of RFCs), we feel 
        the <xref target="json-rfc-8259" format="none" sectionFormat="bare">JSON 
        RFC 8259</xref>, has left significant ambiguity. Should currency be 
        transmitted and serialized as JSON strings using <xref 
        target="bigdecimal-java-oracle" format="none" sectionFormat="bare">Java 
        style BigDecimals</xref> or <xref target="bigdecimal-mclaughlin" 
        format="none" sectionFormat="bare">BigDecimal clones</xref>, which are 
        NOT any kind of IETF standard? Or should the various parsers and 
        serializers be fixed and standardized to use JSON numbers?
      </t>
      <t>
        For more details on these ambiguities related to <xref 
        target="json-rfc-8259" format="none" sectionFormat="bare">JSON</xref> ;
      </t>
      <t>
        <xref target="ten64-commentary" format="none" sectionFormat="bare">@see 
        Ten64 Commentary</xref>
      </t>

      <section anchor="the-ten10b-acronym">
        <name>The Ten10b Acronym</name>
        <t>
          S Morgan:
        </t>
        <t>
          In an attempt to improve human audibility, I added a small b at the 
          end of the acronym. It seemed to have a nice ring to it, like two 21B.
        </t>
      </section>

